#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/textures.rst:12
msgid ""
"When a new lamp is added, it produces light in a uniform, flat color. While "
"this might be sufficient in simple renderings, more sophisticated effects "
"can be accomplished through the use of :doc:`textures </render/"
"blender_render/textures/index>`. Subtle textures can add visual nuance to a "
"lamp, while hard textures can be used to simulate more pronounced effects, "
"such as a disco ball, dappled sunlight breaking through treetops, or even a "
"projector. These textures are assigned to one of ten channels, and behave "
"exactly like material textures, except that they affect a lamp's color and "
"intensity, rather than a material's surface characteristics."
msgstr ""
"Quand une nouvelle lamp est ajoutée, elle produit de la lumière dans une "
"couleur uniforme et plate. Bien que cela puisse être suffisant dans les "
"rendus simples, des effets plus sophistiqués peuvent être accomplis via "
"l'utilisation de :doc:`textures </render/blender_render/textures/index>`. "
"Des textures subtiles peuvent ajouter une nuance visuelle à une lampe, alors "
"que des textures dures peuvent être utilisées pour simuler des effets plus "
"prononcés, tels qu'un discoball, *dappled sunlight breaking through "
"treetops* ou même un projecteur. Ces textures sont assignées à un des dix "
"canaux, et se comportent exactement comme les textures de matériau, sauf "
"qu'ils affecent la couleur et l'intensité d'une lampe, plutôt que les "
"caractéristiques de surface du matériau.   "

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/textures.rst:23
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/textures.rst:25
msgid ""
"The lamp textures settings are grouped into two panels. Here we will only "
"talk about the few things that differ from object material textures; see "
"the :doc:`Materials </render/blender_render/materials/index>` and :doc:"
"`Textures </render/blender_render/textures/index>` chapters for details "
"about the standard options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/textures.rst:30
msgid ""
"The texture-specific and the *Mapping* panels remain the same. However, you "
"will note there are much fewer *Mapping* options. You can only choose "
"between *Global*, *View* or another *Object* 's texture *coordinates* (since "
"a lamp has no texture coordinates by itself), and you can scale or offset "
"the texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/textures.rst:35
msgid ""
"The *Mapping* panel is also a subset of its regular material's counterpart. "
"You can only map a lamp texture to its regular, basic *Color* and/or to its "
"*Shadow* color. As you can only affect colors, and a lamp has no texture "
"coordinates on its own, the *Diffuse*, *Specular*, *Shading*, and *Geometry* "
"options have disappeared."
msgstr ""
